<subSubSection pageId="14" pageNumber="15" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1802,2045]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1802,1829]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Aedeagal sheath with two sclerotized, marginally serrated postgonites on anterior portion of left lateral lobe (“ 
<figureCitation box="[226,295,1839,1865]" captionStart="FIGURE 9" captionStartId="32.[151,250,1936,1961]" captionTargetBox="[166,1420,633,1909]" captionTargetId="figure@32.[166,1420,633,1910]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURE 9. Phortica (Ashima) takehiroi Toda, sp. nov. (♂ paratype). A, Head (caudal view); B, antenna; C, palpus and prob- ocsis; D, prementum; E, abdominal sternites; F, periphallic organs (caudolateral view); G–I, phallic organs (lateral, ventrolateral and ventral views, respectively). Scale bars: 0.1 mm in B–D, F–I; 0.5 mm in A, E." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3884632" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3884632/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Fig. 9</figureCitation>
” in 
<bibRefCitation author="Tsacas &amp; Okada" box="[341,591,1839,1865]" firstAuthor="Tsacas" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" pagination="228 - 237" refId="ref37303" refString="Tsacas, L. &amp; Okada, T. (1983) On the Oriental and New Guinean species of the genus Amiota Loew originally described by Duda as Phortica foliiseta, with descriptions of three new species (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Kontyu, 51, 228 - 237." type="journal article" year="1983">Tsacas &amp; Okada 1983</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="14.[151,1437,1802,2045]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,526,1874,1901]" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">Supplementary description</emphasis>
(not repeating characters common to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Chen in Chen &amp; Maca" authorityYear="2012" box="[966,1104,1875,1901]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Phortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="14" pageNumber="15" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="biclavata">
<emphasis box="[966,983,1876,1901]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1000,1104,1875,1901]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="15">biclavata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). Supracervical setae 12–14. Dorsomedial, tentorial apodeme 2/5 as long as basal, parallel portion of dorsolateral, tentorial apodeme. Cibarial, medial sensilla 9–11 per side; posterior sensilla approximately 6 per side.
</paragraph>
